Three kidnapped seminarians of Good Shepherd Major Seminary, Kakau along Abuja /Kaduna Highway have been released. Their release was contained in a statement signed by the Registrar of the school, Reverend father Joel Usman and made available to the press on Friday. The statement, however, said one of the abducted seminarian is still at large, while thanking Nigerians who prayed for their safe release, the statement urged Nigerians to continue to pray for the release of the remaining one. The statement read, “With joy, the Formators, Staff and Seminarians of Good Shepherd Major Seminary, Kaduna, Kaduna State, announce the safe release of 3 of our Seminarians by their captors. Nigerian Breweries renovate classrooms, toilets in Kaduna… President confirms Salih-Farah as substantive NITT DG NPA donates furniture to primary school in Kaduna El-rufai launches 1,000 milk farm project in Kubau ALSO READ: End cultism or resign, Gov Bello warns heads of tertiary institutions, CSOs “One is still at large. We thank you our brothers and sisters for your prayers in our travails. Kindly continue to pray for the remaining one and all those who are still in the hands of Kidnappers.” As at the time of filing this report it was not known whether a ransom was paid before their release. It will be recalled that suspected Kidnappers had stormed the school on 8th January 2020 between the hours of 10.30 pm and 11 pm and abducted the students. Since then the school had been making frantic efforts for their release. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE. PREMATURE EJACULATION, SMALL SIZE FINALLY CURED NAT